ForgeRegistryTagManager
public interface ITagManager<V> extends Iterable<ITag<V>>
A tag manager holds information about all tags currently bound to a forge registry. This should be preferred to any Holder-related methods.

  • Methodendetails

    • getTag

      @NotNull @NotNull ITag<V> getTag(@NotNull @NotNull TagKey<V> name)
      Queries this tag manager for a tag with the given tag key. If it does not exist, this will create an empty tag and return it.
      Siehe auch:
      • isKnownTagName(TagKey)
      API Note:
      This method guarantees that all future calls to this method on the same tag manager instance with the same tag key will return the same tag.

    • getReverseTag

      @NotNull @NotNull Optional<IReverseTag<V>> getReverseTag(@NotNull V value)
      Queries a reverse tag for a given value from the forge registry linked to this tag manager. A reverse tag stores all tags that the given value is contained in.
      Parameter:
      value - A value currently registered to the forge registry linked to this tag manager
      Gibt zurück:
      A reverse tag for the given value, or an empty optional if the value is not registered

    • isKnownTagName

      boolean isKnownTagName(@NotNull @NotNull TagKey<V> name)
      Checks whether the given tag key exists in this tag manager and is bound. Unlike getTag(TagKey), this method will not create the tag if it does not exist.

    • createOptionalTagKey

      @NotNull @NotNull TagKey<V> createOptionalTagKey(@NotNull @NotNull ResourceLocation location, @NotNull @NotNull Set<? extends Supplier<V>> defaults)
      Creates a tag key that will use the set of defaults if the tag is not loaded from any datapacks. Useful on the client side when a server may not provide a specific tag. Custom registries can use DeferredRegister.addOptionalTagDefaults(TagKey, Set) to create tag keys before the tag manager is created.
      Siehe auch:
      • createTagKey(ResourceLocation)
      • addOptionalTagDefaults(TagKey, Set)
      • DeferredRegister.createOptionalTagKey(ResourceLocation, Set)

    • addOptionalTagDefaults

      void addOptionalTagDefaults(@NotNull @NotNull TagKey<V> name, @NotNull @NotNull Set<? extends Supplier<V>> defaults)
      Adds defaults to an existing tag key. The set of defaults will be bound to the tag if the tag is not loaded from any datapacks. Useful on the client side when a server may not provide a specific tag. Custom registries can use DeferredRegister.addOptionalTagDefaults(TagKey, Set) to add defaults before the tag manager is created.

      • createOptionalTagKey(ResourceLocation, Set)
